  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the abilities of high-speed,high-resolution (HR)
      optical coherence tomography (OCT) and Stratus OCT for detection of retinal nerve fiber layer
      (RNFL) loss in eyes with band atrophy (BA) of the optic nerve.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
